args: A left-handed mercenary wielding a kukri?\nForgive me, but I know nothing of it.
Yeah, no assassins like that ring a bell.\nWhy? You looking to hire?
There's no one like that in\nthe Shadewolves.
Say, Commander? What about\nyou-know-who? That two-bit outlaw.
Zardon? Hmm. Come to think of it, he was\npretty proud of some rare southeastern\nshortblade he'd laid his hands on.
Huh. This is where we arranged to meet,\nbut Ramiel hasn't shown yet.
I got my hands on some good info.\nShould I wait for Ramiel, or...
Caaandy! Get your caaandy here!\nCome and try this sweet, sweet candy!
Well, hello there! You know, ol' Papa Bear\nsure does love him some sweets.
Nevin still hasn't shown? Never a stickler\nfor punctuality, that one.
Caaandy! Get your caaandy here!\nOne taste and you'll be hooked!
Well, she's certainly working hard.\nPerhaps I can reward her with a purchase.
Hold on, bub! White outfit...glasses...\nkinda snooty lookin'... Hot damn!\nYou must be Ramiel!
Er, yes. And how do you know me?
Fella named Nevin gave me a note\nand asked me to pass it on.
You're the one who killed the priest\nwho led Lay the Hands, aren't you?
I ain't got a clue what yer talkin' about.
There's no use playing ignorant;\nthe priest wrote your name in blood.
Bull pucky! There weren't nothin' like that\nwhen I left the chur... Uh...
Heh. Looks like I found the idiot.\nSo where's the magical doodad\nthat you made off with?
Hell, that was careless. Looks like Zardon's\ngonna need to zip that lip for good!
If you wanted to put the screws to me,\nyou shoulda waited until I was alone!\nBwaaa ha ha ha!
Oh, by all means, bring it on.\nBut Papa Bear's pretty strong, you know.
Looks like I was wrong to think ya were\njust some sly little runt.
I don't need your evaluation. Just bring it\non already. You can even use the blade\nyou used to murder the Templar and priest!

See, I might not look like much, but I'm
constantly getting worked by this real nasty
dragonand you people are NO match
for that, let me tell you.
This is the place listed in the note...\nNevin! Are you all right?
Well, look who made it! Too bad I already\nsubdued our new friend here.
Why did you not wait for me?
Because this guy's quick? And his punk\npals really didn't necessitate any backup.
A fact you could only have known in\nhindsight. It is foolish to dive into enemy\nterritory without taking all precautions.
Whoa, come on. I think you're\nselling me a little short here.
From my perspective, you have much yet\nto learnI would have you reflect on that.
Again with you treating me like a kid.\nOr are you just worried about yourself?
We share a Sigil. If I die, so do you.
That was not at all my intent. I am merely\nconcerned for YOUR welfare.
Think nothing of it. Let us pull ourselves\ntogether and continue our work.
Urgh... My head... I'm seein' double...\nNow there's two jerkfaces...!
Sorry to do this right when you're up\nfrom a nap, but it's question time.\nWhere'd you put the gaolstone?
Yeah, not buying that one. Based on the\nevidence in your hideout here, it's clear\nyou were doing business with the priest.
The more intense conflicts become in a\nplace, the more refined the engineering\nfor weapons and magical artifacts.

And so, the priest uses the activities of his
charity as cover on northern battlefields
and conducts market research on said
weapons and magical artifacts.
And once he finds a potential product,\nhe brings you north to acquire the goods\nby whatever means necessary.
Then you bring the goods back down south\nand sell it on the black market to outlaws\nand dilettantes. How we doing so far?

But I imagine the gaolstone commanded a
higher price than anticipated, which led
you to murder the priest and keep all the
profits for yourself.
Looks like this oyster's gone clam.\nMaybe there is some honor among\nthieves after all.
Sadly, we don't have time to deal with\nwhatever fragments of pride remain in\nyour pitiful mind.
Now then, tell us what we want to know\nbefore I say such words that you begin to\ncurse the very day of your birth.
You better do what he says, friend;\nI can't control my partner when he\ngets like this.
B-bring it on! I ain't scared!
Hoo boy. Now you've done it.
Nevin, why don't you go outside\nand have a bit of candy?
Just try not to go too far, all right?
And now for the real fun. Oh ho...
Still got a lot to learn, he says?
How long till he accepts that I'm a\ngrown man who knows what he's doing?
H-hey, c'mon! Ya can't say THAT to me!\nThat's gonna... No! NO! NOOOOOO!
